WEBVTT

00:05.005 --> 00:06.086
Previously on Beyond.

00:06.087 --> 00:09.129
Nothing will distract me
from bringing you home.

00:09.130 --> 00:10.760
So what are you in the mood for?

00:10.761 --> 00:13.843
Something orange.

00:13.844 --> 00:17.097
I see equations broken down
into an infinitesimal level.

00:17.098 --> 00:19.139
You're not some
gypsy fortune teller.

00:19.140 --> 00:20.520
I was in a four-year coma.

00:20.521 --> 00:21.811
Who am I looking at?

00:21.812 --> 00:23.103
Tess Shoemacher.

00:23.104 --> 00:25.105
CFO of Hollow Sky.

00:25.106 --> 00:26.196
Hollow Sky has been alerted

00:26.197 --> 00:28.408
to a young man
with special abilities.

00:28.409 --> 00:31.202
Perhaps you'd be interested
in making a trade.

00:32.783 --> 00:36.035
We will need to recalibrate
our approach, Dr. Frost.

00:36.036 --> 00:38.037
Frost was Arthur's partner?

00:38.038 --> 00:40.920
- You're connected to this machine.
- I can feel it.

00:40.921 --> 00:42.712
Holden!

00:42.713 --> 00:43.874
No!

00:45.426 --> 00:47.467
- Holden, no!
- I had you!

00:47.468 --> 00:49.008
And then you were gone!

00:49.009 --> 00:52.223
I won't risk that ever again.

00:56.056 --> 00:58.349
Come on. This machine
is a death sentence.

01:00.521 --> 01:03.313
How could you do this to me?

01:03.314 --> 01:05.815
I did this for you.

01:05.816 --> 01:07.647
For us.

01:07.648 --> 01:09.028
Look, you almost died in there.

01:09.029 --> 01:10.240
I won't let that happen again.

01:10.241 --> 01:11.861
What are you talking about?

01:11.862 --> 01:14.694
It was like
the ground crumbled. I...

01:14.695 --> 01:17.577
I grabbed your hands. You fell.

01:17.578 --> 01:20.160
Holden, you're not
making any sense.

01:20.161 --> 01:21.122
Yes, I am.

01:21.123 --> 01:23.253
You know I am, but...

01:23.254 --> 01:26.296
The Realm is too dangerous.

01:26.297 --> 01:28.759
We spent all that time running.

01:30.131 --> 01:32.382
Even now that we're back,

01:32.383 --> 01:35.805
after all that's happened,
I... I still can't shake it.

01:35.806 --> 01:40.390
You know as much as I do
we don't belong there.

01:40.391 --> 01:42.603
We belong here.

01:44.185 --> 01:46.816
Finally now we can pick up
where we left off.

01:46.817 --> 01:48.107
We can stay
in one place together.

01:48.108 --> 01:49.319
We don't have to run.

01:49.320 --> 01:51.691
You make it sound so simple.

01:51.692 --> 01:53.944
But it's not just about us.

01:57.037 --> 01:58.499
Was it ever about us?

01:59.950 --> 02:03.003
All our training,
remembering our time together.

02:04.955 --> 02:07.207
It's all so I could
go back in for...

02:07.208 --> 02:08.799
for him? For Arthur?

02:11.592 --> 02:13.754
Holden, what we had was real.

02:15.176 --> 02:17.178
It is real.

02:18.809 --> 02:21.311
It's just...

02:21.312 --> 02:23.354
it's complicated.

02:25.145 --> 02:27.188
Let me know
when you UN-complicate it.

02:28.819 --> 02:30.401
You know where to find me.

02:32.000 --> 02:38.074
